The paper deals with cooperative diversity in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a distributed method for selecting the best relay, which involves system-level considerations and could be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY). The paper mentions the potential implementation of the proposed method in existing radio hardware, which could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM) or cryptography and security (cs.CR) depending on the specific application.
